2017-11-19 Release 1.0.0

Breaking Changes!

Generalize the configuration interface to this module, for better module
maintainability, we render a hash of options to the consul configuration
files.

The following options are therefore removed, use consul_template::config_hash
or consul_template::config_defaults instead:

  consul_template::consul_host
  consul_template::consul_port
  consul_template::consul_token
  consul_template::consul_retry
  consul_template::consul_retry_attempts
  consul_template::consul_retry_backoff
  consul_template::consul_wait
  consul_template::consul_max_stale
  consul_template::deduplicate
  consul_template::deduplicate_prefix
  consul_template::log_level
  consul_template::vault_enabled
  consul_template::vault_address
  consul_template::vault_token
  consul_template::vault_ssl
  consul_template::vault_ssl_verify
  consul_template::vault_ssl_cert
  consul_template::vault_ssl_ca_cert
  consul_template::consul_reload_signal
  consul_template::consul_kill_signal
  consul_template::consul_ssl_enabled
  consul_template::consul_ssl_verify
  consul_template::consul_ssl_cert
  consul_template::consul_ssl_ca_cert

This module now depends on solarkennedy/puppet-consul for its
consul_sorted_json function.

New configuration options:

  consul_template::consul_template::pretty_config
  consul_template::consul_template::pretty_config_indent
  consul_template::consul_template::config_hash
  consul_template::consul_template::config_defaults

